WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.166 --> 00:00:02.916
[Jubilee] <i>Previously on</i> X-Men...

2
00:00:03.916 --> 00:00:05.165
[Roberto] Please don't hurt me.

3
00:00:05.166 --> 00:00:08.374
I'm Roberto Da Costa.
heir to the Da Costa fortune.

4
00:00:08.375 --> 00:00:09.832
What's this freak's trick?

5
00:00:09.833 --> 00:00:10.957
No clue.

6
00:00:10.958 --> 00:00:13.040
Kid didn't even try to use his powers.

7
00:00:13.041 --> 00:00:14.208
[men grunting]

8
00:00:16.125 --> 00:00:17.499
Good guy or bad guy?

9
00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:19.000
Definitely the good guy.

10
00:00:19.750 --> 00:00:21.875
Your parents don't know. do they?

11
00:00:22.375 --> 00:00:24.207
[Roberto] Some sort of solar energy.

12
00:00:24.208 --> 00:00:26.249
Just reminds me that I'm different.

13
00:00:26.250 --> 00:00:28.082
Be an X-Men. Jubilee?

14
00:00:28.083 --> 00:00:29.500
I don't even want to be myself.

15
00:00:32.166 --> 00:00:33.999
[screams]

16
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:35.832
<i>The breeze is gone.</i>

17
00:00:35.833 --> 00:00:39.124
I cannot feel it. nor the moisture.

18
00:00:39.125 --> 00:00:40.208
nor the air.

19
00:00:41.416 --> 00:00:44.083
- [Hank] The effects appear permanent.
- [gasps]

20
00:00:45.750 --> 00:00:47.207
Name's Forge. Storm.

21
00:00:47.208 --> 00:00:49.874
An old friend of Charles Xavier.

22
00:00:49.875 --> 00:00:52.416
I'd like to help you
get back what you've lost.

23
00:00:54.291 --> 00:00:56.125
[♪ theme music playing]

24
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:04.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

25
00:02:11.541 --> 00:02:13.457
Gambit found a little extra.

26
00:02:13.458 --> 00:02:15.540
Here. take some cream with it.

27
00:02:15.541 --> 00:02:17.790
Aw. thanks. Remy. You're sweet.

28
00:02:17.791 --> 00:02:20.124
But our new boss beat you to the pot.

29
00:02:20.125 --> 00:02:21.375
It's three sugars.

30
00:02:22.666 --> 00:02:25.416
I'll take a cappuccino
if you just takin' orders.

31
00:02:25.916 --> 00:02:28.750
No. Luckily. I am giving them.

32
00:02:29.333 --> 00:02:33.207
After breakfast. the X-Men will report
to the Danger Room for drills.

33
00:02:33.208 --> 00:02:35.916
We must be ready
should Mister Sinister resurface.

34
00:02:36.416 --> 00:02:38.874
Surely our youngest member
deserves some jubilation

35
00:02:38.875 --> 00:02:40.832
on her 18th birthday.

36
00:02:40.833 --> 00:02:42.999
I second the blue Rogaine ad.

37
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.082
Kid deserves it.

38
00:02:44.083 --> 00:02:46.249
Jubilee will see far more birthdays

39
00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:50.457
should she learn to master her powers
to face a world that despises her.

40
00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:54.541
Yo-ho! Someone's daddy
didn't get him a pony for his sweet 16th.

41
00:02:55.041 --> 00:02:58.208
My parents perished when I was a child.

42
00:02:59.500 --> 00:03:03.624
Who's got two thumbs that blast fireworks
and turns 18 today?

43
00:03:03.625 --> 00:03:04.707
Me.

44
00:03:04.708 --> 00:03:07.166
Aw. happy birthday. sweet pea.

45
00:03:07.666 --> 00:03:10.166
Boy. do we got some surprises for you.

46
00:03:10.708 --> 00:03:14.207
But first. how do you wanna celebrate
the big 18th. huh?

47
00:03:14.208 --> 00:03:16.540
We are all ears.

48
00:03:16.541 --> 00:03:18.708
Big shocker. I know.

49
00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:20.457
but let's go to the arcade.

50
00:03:20.458 --> 00:03:22.124
It'll be just like old times.

51
00:03:22.125 --> 00:03:23.250
What do we think?

52
00:03:25.166 --> 00:03:28.457
- [Magneto groans]
- "You would have the master of magnetism

53
00:03:28.458 --> 00:03:31.374
"seen in a bar of childish make-believe?"

54
00:03:31.375 --> 00:03:33.374
Ugh! This is bogus.

55
00:03:33.375 --> 00:03:34.915
What's wrong with just one day

56
00:03:34.916 --> 00:03:37.124
where I don't have to freak out
about the Professor.

57
00:03:37.125 --> 00:03:38.832
or Jean and her clone.

58
00:03:38.833 --> 00:03:41.124
or Cyclops and his latest control issue?

59
00:03:41.125 --> 00:03:44.374
They aren't even here because
they just had to go play mutant politics

60
00:03:44.375 --> 00:03:45.790
at the United Nations.

61
00:03:45.791 --> 00:03:48.832
Genosha entering the UN is a big deal.

62
00:03:48.833 --> 00:03:52.333
[scoffs] Small fries.
I'm the birthday Big Mac.

63
00:03:53.541 --> 00:03:55.624
You actually do play video games?

64
00:03:55.625 --> 00:03:57.665
Uh. this might be make-or-break.

65
00:03:57.666 --> 00:04:01.083
The only people who hate video games
are bad at video games.

66
00:04:01.625 --> 00:04:04.041
But actually. this one isn't mine.

67
00:04:04.625 --> 00:04:06.708
Never even heard of a "Motendo."

68
00:04:07.791 --> 00:04:09.457
Rogue said they had some surprises.

69
00:04:09.458 --> 00:04:11.165
Day is looking up. Let's play!

70
00:04:11.166 --> 00:04:13.749
I'd rather <i>minha mãe</i> find out I'm a mutant

71
00:04:13.750 --> 00:04:15.958
than be caught dead playing <i>that.</i>

72
00:04:18.041 --> 00:04:20.875
- [♪ start up music plays]
- [Jubilee] Whoa! What's it doing?

73
00:04:22.041 --> 00:04:23.250
- Hey!
- Whoa!

74
00:04:23.750 --> 00:04:25.583
[both grunt]

75
00:04:27.416 --> 00:04:29.541
[yelps. grunts]

76
00:04:37.750 --> 00:04:40.083
- [Roberto grunts]
- What time is it?

77
00:04:40.583 --> 00:04:42.000
How long were we playing?

78
00:04:42.625 --> 00:04:43.750
I assume I won?

79
00:04:44.458 --> 00:04:45.875
- [metal clanging]
- Wait.

80
00:04:46.291 --> 00:04:49.125
- [screams]
- Hey. let him go!

81
00:04:51.375 --> 00:04:53.625
Whoa! Where'd the mansion go?

82
00:04:59.250 --> 00:05:01.082
[Roberto grunting]

83
00:05:01.083 --> 00:05:03.291
How did we get downtown so fast?

84
00:05:04.416 --> 00:05:05.458
Oh. boy!

85
00:05:09.291 --> 00:05:10.291
[robot chimes]

86
00:05:24.500 --> 00:05:28.207
You know. it would be a lot easier
if you just used your powers.

87
00:05:28.208 --> 00:05:29.624
What if there's cameras around?

88
00:05:29.625 --> 00:05:30.999
My parents could see me on TV.

89
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:32.457
- Die. mutie!
- Die. mutie!

90
00:05:32.458 --> 00:05:34.874
Do you really think
everyone is focused on you?

91
00:05:34.875 --> 00:05:36.041
[Roberto] Yes.

92
00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:44.750
[phone rings]

93
00:05:45.875 --> 00:05:47.957
[Jubilee] Wait a second.
It could be a trap.

94
00:05:47.958 --> 00:05:50.041
A phone booth trap? That'd be creative.

95
00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:51.500
Hello?

96
00:05:59.250 --> 00:06:02.500
- [game beeps]
- Whoa! Hold up. Genosha?

97
00:06:03.083 --> 00:06:05.083
But. like. way-back-when Genosha?

98
00:06:05.791 --> 00:06:06.916
What the heck?

99
00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:09.125
I was trapped here with Storm.

100
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.041
Gambit. too.

101
00:06:11.708 --> 00:06:13.332
And a bunch of other mutants.

102
00:06:13.333 --> 00:06:15.957
All enslaved to build by Bolivar Trask.

103
00:06:15.958 --> 00:06:18.124
[Roberto] The dude
who created the Sentinels?

104
00:06:18.125 --> 00:06:19.541
- [gun fires]
- [gasps]

105
00:06:21.541 --> 00:06:23.166
[man 1] Move in! Fire!

106
00:06:23.833 --> 00:06:24.915
- Halt!
- [man 2] Take 'em down!

107
00:06:24.916 --> 00:06:26.207
[man 1] Go! Go!

108
00:06:26.208 --> 00:06:27.791
[men groaning]

109
00:06:31.541 --> 00:06:32.541
I didn't do that.

110
00:06:33.083 --> 00:06:34.458
Maybe it was...

111
00:06:35.041 --> 00:06:36.041
her.

112
00:06:36.541 --> 00:06:39.082
Was that you. Hot Topic stalker.

113
00:06:39.083 --> 00:06:40.833
calling us earlier on the phone?

114
00:06:46.791 --> 00:06:48.031
[automated voice] <i>System error.</i>

115
00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:49.666
<i>System error.</i>

116
00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:53.000
[Jubilee gasps] Like a cyberpunk mirage.

117
00:06:54.583 --> 00:06:57.832
Duh! We are totally in a video game.

118
00:06:57.833 --> 00:06:58.915
We're what?

119
00:06:58.916 --> 00:07:00.874
Pay attention to the young lady.

120
00:07:00.875 --> 00:07:03.499
You're. like. "totally in a video game."

121
00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:05.000
Love the "totally."

122
00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:08.333
Just what I was hoping for.
Classic Jubilee.

123
00:07:08.958 --> 00:07:12.082
What in the name of all heaven is that?

124
00:07:12.083 --> 00:07:13.165
Mojo here.

125
00:07:13.166 --> 00:07:17.165
your primetime psycho
interdimensional alien TV producer

126
00:07:17.166 --> 00:07:18.707
who feeds off ratings.

127
00:07:18.708 --> 00:07:19.915
My greatest hit?

128
00:07:19.916 --> 00:07:22.457
Putting the X-Men through
overly complicated death traps

129
00:07:22.458 --> 00:07:24.083
to entertain my slaves...

130
00:07:24.666 --> 00:07:26.666
"Indentured audiences." sorry.

131
00:07:27.250 --> 00:07:29.500
Looks like you've been dieting?

132
00:07:30.375 --> 00:07:31.582
You noticed!

133
00:07:31.583 --> 00:07:33.125
Got some nip. some tuck.

134
00:07:33.958 --> 00:07:35.874
Actually. it's been
a horrible third quarter

135
00:07:35.875 --> 00:07:38.165
and it shows. let's be real.

136
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.082
Ratings are down. down. down.

137
00:07:40.083 --> 00:07:44.041
and I'm thirsty for the next big thing.
dirty girl. [chuckles]

138
00:07:44.583 --> 00:07:48.249
That's why I made the pivot
to video games.

139
00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:51.375
The future of mind-numbery!

140
00:07:52.041 --> 00:07:55.290
You're not just <i>in</i> a video game. honey.

141
00:07:55.291 --> 00:07:58.207
You're the star!

142
00:07:58.208 --> 00:08:02.249
Player <i>numero uno</i>
of my first blockbuster release.

143
00:08:02.250 --> 00:08:05.332
where every level
is based off your own memories.

144
00:08:05.333 --> 00:08:07.540
<i>Really? Me? Please.</i>

145
00:08:07.541 --> 00:08:09.665
Big names are a fortune.

146
00:08:09.666 --> 00:08:11.124
Dazzler had a gig. don't ask.

147
00:08:11.125 --> 00:08:15.249
So you're my gamer girl in a gamer world.

148
00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:17.915
You connect with the youth.
You're their point of view.

149
00:08:17.916 --> 00:08:20.749
Picture this. the future of Motendo.

150
00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:22.207
that's "mo" for "Mojo."

151
00:08:22.208 --> 00:08:26.249
in every home. on every world.
in every dimension! Hah!

152
00:08:26.250 --> 00:08:28.540
Zapping up nom-nom-nom

153
00:08:28.541 --> 00:08:30.957
energy from the brains of all who play!

154
00:08:30.958 --> 00:08:35.915
I'll dominate the galaxies
and the 18-to-45 age demographic.

155
00:08:35.916 --> 00:08:38.040
And what if we refuse to play your game?

156
00:08:38.041 --> 00:08:40.165
What then? None of this is even real.

157
00:08:40.166 --> 00:08:42.832
Well. I don't want to say something scary.

158
00:08:42.833 --> 00:08:46.625
like. "If you die in the game.
you die in real life." but...

159
00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:49.625
[cackles] Stakes.

160
00:08:50.125 --> 00:08:54.250
Turn those frowns upside down
before I cut you like a one-hit wonder.

161
00:08:54.750 --> 00:08:56.790
This is the dream. Jubilee.
Be young forever.

162
00:08:56.791 --> 00:08:59.625
replay the golden hits. no growing up.

163
00:09:00.416 --> 00:09:02.165
Think about it. Jubes.

164
00:09:02.166 --> 00:09:05.540
The old X-Men are totally old-school.

165
00:09:05.541 --> 00:09:07.624
<i>Who's the Boss?</i> Magneto.

166
00:09:07.625 --> 00:09:09.290
Storm. <i>Different Worlds.</i>

167
00:09:09.291 --> 00:09:11.999
<i>Divorce Court: Summers v. Grey.</i>

168
00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:13.750
That's not X-Men.

169
00:09:14.583 --> 00:09:15.583
You...

170
00:09:15.584 --> 00:09:18.208
You're my X-Men. Jubilee. so...

171
00:09:19.166 --> 00:09:20.166
Game on!

172
00:09:21.291 --> 00:09:24.333
- [Magneto cackles]
- [crowd cheers]

173
00:09:29.916 --> 00:09:31.791
[Jubilee] It's loading. Here we go.

174
00:09:48.083 --> 00:09:51.500
[Jubilee] <i>All right!</i> [grunting]

175
00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:56.208
[crowd cheering]

176
00:09:58.750 --> 00:10:00.125
[grunts in frustration]

177
00:10:02.875 --> 00:10:03.958
[Roberto] <i>Savage Land?</i>

178
00:10:15.166 --> 00:10:17.958
- [booing]
- [exclaims]

179
00:10:18.416 --> 00:10:19.416
[grunts]

180
00:10:28.583 --> 00:10:29.791
[yelling]

181
00:10:31.333 --> 00:10:32.541
[Spiral] She's at it again.

182
00:10:33.708 --> 00:10:35.540
Patch that bug. Spiral!

183
00:10:35.541 --> 00:10:37.624
This is what you get
when you kill tech support.

184
00:10:37.625 --> 00:10:39.874
For failing to kill the bug!

185
00:10:39.875 --> 00:10:41.290
Nothing lost.

186
00:10:41.291 --> 00:10:42.707
Now. shush!

187
00:10:42.708 --> 00:10:43.790
My favorite level.

188
00:10:43.791 --> 00:10:45.916
[crowd cheering]

189
00:10:51.208 --> 00:10:53.707
I remember seeing this place
on the news with <i>minha mãe.</i>

190
00:10:53.708 --> 00:10:57.207
Magneto's old base
from his megalomaniacal phase.

191
00:10:57.208 --> 00:10:59.082
I acted like I hated mutants.

192
00:10:59.083 --> 00:11:01.040
<i>Minha mãe</i> tried saying
there were good ones.

193
00:11:01.041 --> 00:11:02.540
but I could tell she was spooked.

194
00:11:02.541 --> 00:11:06.040
So I said. "They're all freaks.
and normal people would win."

195
00:11:06.041 --> 00:11:08.499
Man. talk about simpler times.

196
00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:10.707
Now. helmet head's bossing us around

197
00:11:10.708 --> 00:11:12.915
and telling me how to spend my birthday.

198
00:11:12.916 --> 00:11:14.040
It's unreal.

199
00:11:14.041 --> 00:11:16.165
We should probably find a way out of here.

200
00:11:16.166 --> 00:11:17.374
What's the rush?

201
00:11:17.375 --> 00:11:19.291
These levels are taking me back.

202
00:11:20.291 --> 00:11:22.207
Jubes. listen to yourself.

203
00:11:22.208 --> 00:11:23.582
None of this is real.

204
00:11:23.583 --> 00:11:25.500
Sooner or later. you gotta grow up.

205
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:28.458
Otherwise. reality will smack you
right in the face... Ahhh!

206
00:11:31.541 --> 00:11:32.666
[Jubilee] Roberto.

207
00:11:35.041 --> 00:11:37.375
This talky-talky scene is taking forever.

208
00:11:37.916 --> 00:11:40.708
It's boss battle time. babies.

209
00:11:42.708 --> 00:11:44.750
I am Magneto.

210
00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:49.875
[grunts]

211
00:11:51.125 --> 00:11:53.375
Oh. no. Roberto's health is almost gone.

212
00:11:53.875 --> 00:11:54.875
He's dying.

213
00:11:56.416 --> 00:11:58.374
Okay. he's got a pattern of attack.

214
00:11:58.375 --> 00:12:00.082
Typical boss battle shenanigans.

215
00:12:00.083 --> 00:12:02.208
I just need to wait for it to cycle.

216
00:12:04.208 --> 00:12:05.250
[grunts]

217
00:12:07.916 --> 00:12:09.083
One more.

218
00:12:11.708 --> 00:12:12.791
[Magneto cackles]

219
00:12:13.583 --> 00:12:16.624
- [grunts]
- [Magneto groans]

220
00:12:16.625 --> 00:12:17.708
[cackles]

221
00:12:19.791 --> 00:12:20.791
[yells]

222
00:12:27.125 --> 00:12:28.125
Roberto!

223
00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:31.457
No. no. no.

224
00:12:31.458 --> 00:12:32.958
This can't be happening.

225
00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:39.250
Is that

226
00:12:39.708 --> 00:12:40.708
an extra life?

227
00:12:41.958 --> 00:12:44.415
How did that get in there?

228
00:12:44.416 --> 00:12:48.875
Spiral. I thought I told you
to get rid of her.

229
00:12:50.041 --> 00:12:51.333
[scoffs]

230
00:12:53.041 --> 00:12:54.916
[gasps] Did I die?

231
00:12:55.625 --> 00:12:56.625
Was I dead?

232
00:12:56.626 --> 00:12:58.249
Oh. thank goodness.

233
00:12:58.250 --> 00:12:59.625
I thought I lost you.

234
00:13:00.208 --> 00:13:01.707
I found an extra life.

235
00:13:01.708 --> 00:13:03.832
Someone is definitely helping us.

236
00:13:03.833 --> 00:13:06.041
[speaking Portuguese]

237
00:13:10.125 --> 00:13:13.458
I don't speak justifiably
angry Portuguese. but I know.

238
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.708
I messed up. big time.

239
00:13:16.916 --> 00:13:20.083
Still. this young lady
did take down old Magneto.

240
00:13:20.791 --> 00:13:24.958
Bow before the lord of magnetism.

241
00:13:28.208 --> 00:13:29.333
[Roberto] Whoa!

242
00:13:30.625 --> 00:13:31.790
Hey!

243
00:13:31.791 --> 00:13:33.000
[Roberto screams]

244
00:13:37.958 --> 00:13:39.000
Huh?

245
00:13:41.166 --> 00:13:42.874
[woman] No need for thank you
among friends.

246
00:13:42.875 --> 00:13:44.250
And by friends. I mean you.

247
00:13:44.875 --> 00:13:46.582
I hacked you out of the game server

248
00:13:46.583 --> 00:13:49.832
and into Mojo's broadcast servers
to buy us some time.

249
00:13:49.833 --> 00:13:51.374
She's a plot twist.

250
00:13:51.375 --> 00:13:52.583
She's in league with Mojo.

251
00:13:53.166 --> 00:13:54.416
[both] Zip it. Da Costa.

252
00:13:55.708 --> 00:14:00.125
[chuckles] Like I said. we go way back.

253
00:14:02.166 --> 00:14:03.499
Now. we need to move.

254
00:14:03.500 --> 00:14:06.499
That blobby tyrant fraud
could download in here any second

255
00:14:06.500 --> 00:14:09.040
and then rip us back
into his game of deception.

256
00:14:09.041 --> 00:14:10.665
Gonna hit pause here for a second.

257
00:14:10.666 --> 00:14:11.999
I got a few questions.

258
00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:13.999
Explain everything.

259
00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:16.125
You gotta test a game before launch.

260
00:14:16.875 --> 00:14:19.665
Running endless trial loops
with you two was too risky.

261
00:14:19.666 --> 00:14:22.165
So Mojo needed beta testers.

262
00:14:22.166 --> 00:14:23.915
digital replicas of me.

263
00:14:23.916 --> 00:14:25.540
I'm the only one left.

264
00:14:25.541 --> 00:14:27.625
I've played these levels inside and out.

265
00:14:27.791 --> 00:14:30.457
Relived the glory days
more than I care to count.

266
00:14:30.458 --> 00:14:32.875
but note the hair and wrinkles.

267
00:14:33.833 --> 00:14:36.499
Before Mojo killed the beta.
I figured out a glitch

268
00:14:36.500 --> 00:14:38.665
and hacked my way through here
before deletion.

269
00:14:38.666 --> 00:14:40.499
Figures my game has cheat codes.

270
00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:41.625
Very me.

271
00:14:42.333 --> 00:14:47.000
[sighs] Jubilee. I know a part of you
wants to hang here.

272
00:14:47.750 --> 00:14:50.750
It's nice knowing how every stage ends.

273
00:14:51.375 --> 00:14:53.582
No surprises. no twists.

274
00:14:53.583 --> 00:14:55.125
It always stays the same.

275
00:14:55.708 --> 00:14:57.000
But that's not living.

276
00:14:57.583 --> 00:15:00.666
Living doesn't get cheat codes
or extra lives.

277
00:15:01.166 --> 00:15:03.250
But it has friends and family.

278
00:15:03.833 --> 00:15:06.875
Love. loss and heapings of hope.

279
00:15:07.375 --> 00:15:09.833
Life's a total risk and it's on you.

280
00:15:10.375 --> 00:15:11.375
Take it.

281
00:15:12.875 --> 00:15:15.082
So. Magneto was right?

282
00:15:15.083 --> 00:15:18.415
A bit. but he's totally wrong
about one thing.

283
00:15:18.416 --> 00:15:19.625
Video games rule.

284
00:15:22.041 --> 00:15:24.499
Now. what do you say
we destroy Mojo's game

285
00:15:24.500 --> 00:15:26.415
and get you two lovebirds out of here?

286
00:15:26.416 --> 00:15:27.875
[game beeping]

287
00:15:32.166 --> 00:15:33.707
Two Jubilees?

288
00:15:33.708 --> 00:15:34.791
Cheaters!

289
00:15:35.291 --> 00:15:37.333
[crowd shouting]

290
00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:42.540
Guys. I think he fell off his diet.

291
00:15:42.541 --> 00:15:43.790
Fine by me.

292
00:15:43.791 --> 00:15:45.041
The bigger they are...

293
00:15:46.666 --> 00:15:48.208
the harder they pop.

294
00:15:53.291 --> 00:15:54.707
Wow! I can do that?

295
00:15:54.708 --> 00:15:57.666
[Abscissa]
That ain't the half of it. Just you wait.

296
00:15:59.541 --> 00:16:01.000
[groans]

297
00:16:05.791 --> 00:16:06.791
Whoa! Ah!

298
00:16:07.583 --> 00:16:12.083
What's the testing on throwing
to a commercial during a video game?

299
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:19.041
[Mojo screams]

300
00:16:19.750 --> 00:16:20.832
I got him!

301
00:16:20.833 --> 00:16:22.457
[Abscissa] Hold up. cowboy.

302
00:16:22.458 --> 00:16:24.916
It ain't over till the fat despot sings.

303
00:16:25.958 --> 00:16:29.541
[Mojo] Time to end you nasty glitches.

304
00:16:38.875 --> 00:16:41.082
You brats may have canceled me today.

305
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:44.958
but I swear. I'll gut you in the reboot.

306
00:16:49.166 --> 00:16:50.208
[screams]

307
00:16:56.875 --> 00:16:58.458
[crowd cheers]

308
00:17:11.458 --> 00:17:13.541
[electrical buzzing]

309
00:17:14.083 --> 00:17:18.083
- Roberto. you could've...
- Yeah. talk about risk.

310
00:17:46.166 --> 00:17:47.875
[Forge] Storm. dinner is ready.

311
00:17:58.583 --> 00:18:00.250
My papa's bison chili.

312
00:18:01.125 --> 00:18:02.166
It's a leaner cut.

313
00:18:02.708 --> 00:18:05.166
Gives room for the spices
to do their magic.

314
00:18:07.541 --> 00:18:08.666
You're very kind.

315
00:18:09.250 --> 00:18:11.666
Well. a friend of Charles Xavier
is a friend of mine.

316
00:18:12.166 --> 00:18:14.083
I owe that fellow a great deal.

317
00:18:14.791 --> 00:18:15.833
As do we all.

318
00:18:16.916 --> 00:18:18.249
How does it work.

319
00:18:18.250 --> 00:18:21.000
a mutant who can invent
anything he can conceive?

320
00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:24.999
I can get at parts of the brain
that are normally dormant in humans.

321
00:18:25.000 --> 00:18:26.874
Draw unique connections.

322
00:18:26.875 --> 00:18:28.415
see how bits fit.

323
00:18:28.416 --> 00:18:31.207
like a Rubik's Cube on constant autopilot.

324
00:18:31.208 --> 00:18:32.874
Or simply a genius.

325
00:18:32.875 --> 00:18:35.666
Well. life and love. God help me.

326
00:18:36.375 --> 00:18:37.874
But if you're needing a neat toaster

327
00:18:37.875 --> 00:18:40.207
or a thing that'll store
your mutant powers...

328
00:18:40.208 --> 00:18:42.540
Or a bowl of this delicious chili.

329
00:18:42.541 --> 00:18:44.583
[laughs] Yep. or chili.

330
00:18:45.166 --> 00:18:46.250
Then I'm your man.

331
00:18:54.958 --> 00:18:56.375
[Ororo] May I ask?

332
00:18:57.625 --> 00:18:58.625
[Forge] I was a soldier.

333
00:18:59.458 --> 00:19:00.583
and there was a war.

334
00:19:02.833 --> 00:19:04.207
I miss soaring.

335
00:19:04.208 --> 00:19:08.290
The wind in my hair.
so powerful it's hard to breathe.

336
00:19:08.291 --> 00:19:10.791
but so fresh as to be worth it.

337
00:19:11.250 --> 00:19:14.166
Your mutant gifts
have allowed you to fix yourself.

338
00:19:14.958 --> 00:19:16.124
What a blessing.

339
00:19:16.125 --> 00:19:17.749
[Forge] Wasn't anything to fix.

340
00:19:17.750 --> 00:19:21.000
Just adapted and got a little creative.

341
00:19:23.458 --> 00:19:24.541
Let's go for a ride.

342
00:19:28.750 --> 00:19:30.416
[hooves clopping]

343
00:19:40.750 --> 00:19:42.291
[Forge] Looks like you got creative.

344
00:19:44.208 --> 00:19:45.208
Keep up.

345
00:19:45.708 --> 00:19:47.666
I'm not building you a faster horse.

346
00:19:49.208 --> 00:19:51.125
What a rude little man.

347
00:19:56.583 --> 00:19:57.583
[Forge laughs]

348
00:20:02.958 --> 00:20:04.249
[gasps]

349
00:20:04.250 --> 00:20:05.500
[whinnies]

350
00:20:08.916 --> 00:20:11.291
[chuckles] The goddess lives.

351
00:20:12.250 --> 00:20:13.625
Beautiful. isn't it?

352
00:20:14.125 --> 00:20:16.708
[owl hooting softly]

353
00:20:18.750 --> 00:20:21.708
[Ororo] That owl.
I've seen him before. circling.

354
00:20:22.208 --> 00:20:23.875
Perhaps he is like the winds.

355
00:20:24.666 --> 00:20:27.165
The moon affects tides and temperatures.

356
00:20:27.166 --> 00:20:29.582
guiding the wind
across our planet's surface.

357
00:20:29.583 --> 00:20:31.624
The winds here never shift.

358
00:20:31.625 --> 00:20:35.916
They always blow east.
stuck like this owl.

359
00:20:37.666 --> 00:20:41.000
[Forge] You more than anyone
know how fast the weather can change.

360
00:20:46.291 --> 00:20:48.832
The real trick to reversing
what the X-Cutioner did to you

361
00:20:48.833 --> 00:20:51.458
wasn't making an inverted version
of its radiation.

362
00:20:52.166 --> 00:20:55.500
[Ororo] It was creating a machine
that could safely channel such power.

363
00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:57.541
Ah! You've been listening.

364
00:20:58.041 --> 00:21:01.332
Last power differential clicked in my head
when we were out riding.

365
00:21:01.333 --> 00:21:02.416
Like I said.

366
00:21:02.958 --> 00:21:04.416
helps to get outside.

367
00:21:05.625 --> 00:21:06.791
You ready?

368
00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:09.916
[breathes deeply]

369
00:21:15.416 --> 00:21:17.666
[Forge] Okay. Ororo. give it a try.

370
00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:19.291
[Ororo] Winds.

371
00:21:19.833 --> 00:21:21.375
heed my command.

372
00:21:27.166 --> 00:21:30.665
I am Storm. mistress of the elements.

373
00:21:30.666 --> 00:21:33.875
Rise. winds. and move the desert sands.

374
00:21:36.333 --> 00:21:37.666
[crows cawing]

375
00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:43.875
Please. winds.

376
00:21:45.458 --> 00:21:46.583
hear me.

377
00:21:47.583 --> 00:21:48.833
[tearfully] Please.

378
00:21:50.625 --> 00:21:52.541
This isn't happening. Forge.

379
00:21:53.166 --> 00:21:54.208
It can't be real.

380
00:21:54.708 --> 00:21:56.125
[Forge] I know. Ororo.

381
00:21:56.875 --> 00:21:57.875
I know.

382
00:22:14.083 --> 00:22:17.000
Oh. You're still working on the machine.

383
00:22:19.583 --> 00:22:22.375
Why is fixing me so important to you?

384
00:22:24.791 --> 00:22:26.207
Storm...

385
00:22:26.208 --> 00:22:27.291
[grunts softly]

386
00:22:28.958 --> 00:22:29.958
After the war.

387
00:22:30.625 --> 00:22:34.708
I didn't have the resources
to build what I so easily saw in my mind.

388
00:22:35.958 --> 00:22:38.125
The Defense Department offered to help me

389
00:22:38.791 --> 00:22:41.000
as long as I helped them
build some devices.

390
00:22:42.916 --> 00:22:44.666
Devices that could be used to

391
00:22:45.250 --> 00:22:47.416
neutralize dangerous mutants.

392
00:22:48.541 --> 00:22:49.624
No.

393
00:22:49.625 --> 00:22:51.208
No. no. no.

394
00:22:51.708 --> 00:22:52.916
You made these?

395
00:22:53.416 --> 00:22:55.916
No. a scientist in Scotland did.

396
00:22:56.416 --> 00:22:59.250
Using my early designs.
rough strokes at best.

397
00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:01.332
I left the government by then.

398
00:23:01.333 --> 00:23:05.625
You of all people should know the perils
of trusting those in Washington.

399
00:23:06.875 --> 00:23:08.083
[Forge] That's not fair.

400
00:23:08.583 --> 00:23:11.708
I was hurting. lost. bitter.

401
00:23:12.250 --> 00:23:13.250
I gave up.

402
00:23:13.875 --> 00:23:15.707
If I told you the truth in Dallas.

403
00:23:15.708 --> 00:23:17.250
you wouldn't have let me help you.

404
00:23:17.708 --> 00:23:19.165
So you lied.

405
00:23:19.166 --> 00:23:20.750
My weaver of lies.

406
00:23:21.208 --> 00:23:22.750
It hasn't all been lies.

407
00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:24.500
This...

408
00:23:25.291 --> 00:23:26.500
This is not a lie.

409
00:23:27.125 --> 00:23:29.583
No. don't you dare.

410
00:23:30.750 --> 00:23:32.041
I could live forever.

411
00:23:32.541 --> 00:23:34.415
And still. my endless imagination

412
00:23:34.416 --> 00:23:37.583
would never conceive
of a thing as perfect as you.

413
00:23:38.416 --> 00:23:40.958
A perfect path to your redemption.

414
00:23:42.125 --> 00:23:43.958
You are a goddess.

415
00:23:45.166 --> 00:23:46.457
Powers be damned.

416
00:23:46.458 --> 00:23:48.000
How do you not see that?

417
00:23:49.208 --> 00:23:50.625
Ororo. look at me.

418
00:23:51.041 --> 00:23:52.041
Look.

419
00:23:52.042 --> 00:23:54.499
I'll say it once. just once.

420
00:23:54.500 --> 00:23:56.375
Then you can go or you can stay. but...

421
00:23:58.666 --> 00:23:59.708
I love you.

422
00:24:01.875 --> 00:24:03.750
You meant to make me a goddess.

423
00:24:04.333 --> 00:24:06.750
Instead. you have fashioned a fool.

424
00:24:09.791 --> 00:24:11.000
[thunder rumbling]

425
00:24:18.041 --> 00:24:19.041
[horse whinnies]

426
00:24:31.416 --> 00:24:32.458
Ororo!

427
00:24:32.958 --> 00:24:34.790
I was just coming upstairs after you.

428
00:24:34.791 --> 00:24:37.708
What? How did I return here?

429
00:24:43.833 --> 00:24:46.541
- [thudding]
- [warbling]

430
00:24:53.583 --> 00:24:55.583
[gasps] By all things in the heavens.

431
00:24:56.208 --> 00:24:58.707
Get out of my home. you damn demon!

432
00:24:58.708 --> 00:24:59.916
[Forge groans]

433
00:25:02.208 --> 00:25:03.416
[Forge grunts]

434
00:25:05.041 --> 00:25:06.915
[Ororo] <i>Is this death?</i>

435
00:25:06.916 --> 00:25:08.750
- [creature] No.
- [thunderclap]

436
00:25:10.458 --> 00:25:11.500
You live.

437
00:25:12.166 --> 00:25:13.541
Disappointed.

438
00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:16.249
Trapped here. haunted.

439
00:25:16.250 --> 00:25:18.749
Suffering. despairing.

440
00:25:18.750 --> 00:25:21.582
I feast on misery.

441
00:25:21.583 --> 00:25:24.458
And I. The Adversary.

442
00:25:25.125 --> 00:25:27.875
shall not waste my meal.

443
00:25:33.791 --> 00:25:36.041
[♪ captivating instrumental music playing]

443
00:25:37.305 --> 00:26:37.238
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-
